    "media:imagetext": "Greetings from a Pan Am Fun Flight!\nI'm on a jet now but I thought you'd enjoy seeing one of\nPan Am's historic Clippers. Pan Am's version of the\nLockheed L-49 \"Constellation\"\nwas the first transat-\nlantic plane to boast a pressurized cabin, which enabled\nit to clear 20,800 feet with 45 passengers. Carrying a\ncrew of eight, a \"Connie\"\nflew\naviation's first sched-\nuled round-the-world flight in 1947.\nSTAMP ME\nWITH AN\nINTERESTING\nSTAMP AND\nTAKE ME TO A\nMAILBOX.\nTo:\n201\n.1217",
